    "As Csíkos and Szitányi's (2020) suggested, PSTs might use their pedagogical content knowledge to generate multiple approaches to solving the problem.",
    "Regarding PSTs' problem-solving strategies, the most frequently used strategy was guess, check, and refine.",
    "This strategy was utilized differently, as demonstrated by PSTs' sample work in Figure 2 and Figure 3.",
    "This finding is consistent with previous research indicating that guess, check, and refine is a common problem-solving strategy children and teachers use (Duru et al., 2011; Verschaffel et al., 2020).",
    "This approach involves making an educated guess, checking the validity of the guess, and refining the solution until an acceptable solution is reached."
